Toss apples and pears with 1 tablespoon (15 ml) flour, 1/4 cup (50 ml) sugar, lemon peel and juice, and nutmeg. Spoon into 9-inch (23-cm) pie plate. Combine remaining flour, remaining 1/4 cup (50 ml) sugar, oats, and cinnamon. Add margarine. Using pastry blender or 2 knives, cut margarine into flour mixture until crumbly. Sprinkle crumbs over fruit Bake at 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) until filling bubbles and topping is browned, about 35 minutes. Cool on a wire rack. Serve warm or cold.